The biggest surprise in this project was that the hard part turned out to be question design, not machine learning. Getting a model to classify worker domain from embeddings was almost too easy, which made it a poor instrument for separating the two intake methods. The sub-clustering visible in Set A's t-SNE projection but absent in Set B's was the most interesting finding, and the fact that it didn't show up in accuracy at all is a good reminder that metrics don't always tell the whole story. If I were to run this again, I'd add more domains, use real respondents instead of synthetic personas, and pick a target feature that's harder to classify. Comfort level with AI turned out to be completely unpredictable from either question set, which is probably where the more interesting work lives.
